# Usage Examples

Collection of common usage patterns for the UNRDF CLI.

## Code Generation Workflow

### 1. Initial Setup

```bash
# Create configuration file
cat > unrdf.toml << EOF
[project]
name = "my-project"

[ontology]
source = "ontology/schema.ttl"

[generation]
output_dir = "src"
EOF
```

### 2. Generate Code

```bash
# Generate all artifacts
unrdf sync

# Preview without writing
unrdf sync --dry-run

# Run specific rule
unrdf sync --rule generate-types
```

### 3. Watch Mode

```bash
# Continuously regenerate as files change
unrdf sync --watch
```

## Validation Workflow

### Validate Single File

```bash
# Basic validation
unrdf validate ontology.nt

# With summary statistics
unrdf validate ontology.nt --summary
```

### Validate for CI/CD

```bash
# JSON output for automation
unrdf validate ontology.nt --json

# Exit code: 0 = valid, 1 = invalid
if unrdf validate ontology.nt; then
  echo "Valid!"
else
  echo "Invalid!"
  exit 1
fi
```

## Format Conversion

### Turtle to N-Triples

```bash
unrdf convert schema.ttl schema.nt
```

### Batch Conversion

```bash
# Convert all Turtle files in a directory
for file in ontology/*.ttl; do
  unrdf convert "$file" "${file%.ttl}.nt"
done
```

## Query Examples

### Count Triples

```bash
unrdf query ontology.nt "SELECT (COUNT(*) as ?count) WHERE { ?s ?p ?o }"
```

### List All Classes

```bash
unrdf query ontology.nt "
SELECT ?class WHERE {
  ?class a rdfs:Class
}
"
```

### Find All Properties

```bash
unrdf query ontology.nt "
SELECT ?prop WHERE {
  ?prop a rdf:Property
}
ORDER BY ?prop
"
```

## Advanced Sync Configuration

### Multiple Ontology Sources

```toml
[ontology]
source = "core/schema.nt"
extra_sources = [
  "extensions/custom.nt",
  "shapes/validation.nt"
]

[generation]
backup_before_overwrite = true
```

### Directory Loading

```toml
[ontology]
source = "ontology/"  # Loads all .nt/.ttl files recursively
```

### Per-Rule Output

```toml
[[generation.rules]]
name = "typescript-types"
template = "templates/ts-types.njk"
output_file = "types/{{ className | pascalCase }}.ts"
mode = "skip_existing"
```

## Troubleshooting

### Debug Template Rendering

```bash
# Enable verbose output
unrdf sync --verbose

# Run single rule
unrdf sync --rule my-rule --verbose
```

### Check Configuration

```bash
# Validate config syntax
unrdf sync --dry-run
```

### File Permission Issues

```bash
# Check if files are readable
ls -la ontology/

# Fix permissions
chmod +r ontology/*.nt
```
